label: Urine collected in 14 day window
definition: Collected with +/- 14 days of ideal date

label: Urine collected in 30 day window
definition: Collected with +/- 30 days of ideal date

label: Duration of urine collection (hrs)
definition: Number of hours urine was collected. The protocol specified 5 hours.

label: Sample analysis date
definition: Date urine sample was analyzed by the lab

label: Greater than 100% mannitol excreted
definition: The sample fails quality control checks since more than 100% of the recorded mannitol dose given to the participant was excreted

label: Greater than 100% lactulose excreted
definition: The sample fails quality control checks since more than 100% of the recorded lactulose dose given to the participant was excreted

label: Duration of urine collection less than 4.5 hrs
definition: Whether urine was collected for less than 4.5 hours. Urine was supposed to be collected for 5 hours.

label: Duration of urine collection greater than 5.5 hrs
definition: Whether urine was collected for more than 5.5 hours. Urine was supposed to be collected for 5 hours.

label: Urine included in lactulose-mannitol analysis
definition: Urine samples were excluded from analysis if either lactulose or mannitol were not detected, if either lactulose or mannitol excretion was mor than 100% of the dosage, if the duration of urine collection was either less than 4.5 hours or more than 5.5 hours, or if there was some other known issue with the sample

label: Adjusted lactulose excreted (%) greater than 90th percentile in Brazil
definition: Brazil data was used to represent the least abnormal gut permiability values. Since there was a small sample size, extreme values could not be transformed into z-scores with precision, so all values above the 90th percentile are indicated here

label: Adjusted mannitol excreted (%) greater than 90th percentile in Brazil
definition: Brazil data was used to represent the least abnormal gut permiability values. Since there was a small sample size, extreme values could not be transformed into z-scores with precision, so all values above the 90th percentile are indicated here

label: Adjusted lactulose/mannitol excretion ratio greater than 90th percentile in Brazil
definition: Brazil data was used to represent the least abnormal gut permiability values. Since there was a small sample size, extreme values could not be transformed into z-scores with precision, so all values above the 90th percentile are indicated here
